# Mimir — env template.
#
# Copy ONLY the lines you want to fill into your local .env (which is
# .gitignore'd). Do not paste real secrets into this file — it is
# committed to the repo as documentation of the env-var contract.
#
# Once you've filled in your real .env, tell me which item to run and
# I'll execute it end-to-end against the credentials present.

# ─── Already present in your .env (don't touch) ────────────────────────
# ANTROPHIC_TOKEN=sk-ant-...                      # Anthropic API key (live scoring)


# ─── 1. AWS KMS provisioning (unlocks: terraform apply, KMS-mode issuer) ────
#
# Create an IAM user with at minimum:
#   kms:CreateKey, kms:CreateAlias, kms:TagResource, kms:Sign,
#   kms:GetPublicKey, kms:DescribeKey,
#   iam:CreatePolicy, iam:CreateRole, iam:AttachRolePolicy.
#
# Once these are set I will:
#   1. Run `terraform apply` in deploy/aws-kms/ → creates KMS Ed25519 key + IAM role
#   2. Restart the issuer with KMS_MODE=aws against the real key
#   3. Confirm /v1/key returns the KMS ARN, run demo.py end-to-end
#
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# Optional — set if you've already created a KMS key manually and want me to
# point the issuer at it without re-provisioning. If empty, I create one.
KMS_KEY_ARN=


# ─── 2. Etherscan source-verify (unlocks: programmatic verify of the contract) ─
#
# Free signup: https://etherscan.io/myapikey
#
# Once set I will:
#   Run scripts/etherscan-verify.py → submit MimirValidationRegistry.sol to
#   Etherscan → poll until the contract page shows "Verified Source".
#
ETHERSCAN_API_KEY=


# ─── 3. AVS-mode Holesky deploy (unlocks: live deploy against real EigenLayer) ─
#
# Holesky public RPCs are 0/5 working as of 2026-05-16. Either:
#   (a) Sign up for Alchemy (free): https://www.alchemy.com/signup and paste
#       your Holesky RPC URL here; OR
#   (b) Switch to Sepolia (works fine; we already deployed permissionless there)
#       and provide the corresponding EigenLayer addresses if any.
#
# EigenLayer Holesky addresses live in:
#   https://github.com/Layr-Labs/eigenlayer-contracts/tree/dev/script/output/holesky
#
# Once these are set I will:
#   1. Re-run cmd/deploy with SERVICE_MANAGER + SLASHER set
#   2. Confirm the new contract has avsModeEnabled() == true
#   3. Run cmd/verify with SKIP_REVOKE=1 (deployer not authorised at real slasher)
#   4. Record the deployed address in docs/deployments.md
#
ALCHEMY_HOLESKY_RPC=
EIGENLAYER_SERVICE_MANAGER=
EIGENLAYER_ALLOCATION_MANAGER=


# ─── 4. (Optional) An auditor's intake form URL or contact email ────────
#
# If you have a specific firm in mind, I'll tailor docs/audit-outreach.md
# to their engagement style and produce a copy-paste-ready first email.
# Just paste the URL OR the contact email below.
#
# Examples:
#   https://www.trailofbits.com/contact
#   audits@openzeppelin.com
#   spearbit@cantina.xyz
#
AUDIT_FIRM_CONTACT=


# ─── 5. (Optional, advanced) Custom historical-keys path for JWK rotation ─
# If you want to test the rotate-key.py flow against your production issuer,
# set the path where the issuer should look up retired keys.
#
ISSUER_HISTORICAL_KEYS_FILE=
